 ) driven by a decline in freshwater supplies, a finding that is underlined by both spectral (white noise) and REDFIT (red noise) analyses. The 550-year pacemaker seems to be an intermediary cycle that may be a derived mode stemming from a rectification of the signal generated by a superposition of the fundamental solar modes (
 
